{{Taxobox | name = Triplecross lizardfish | image = ChouchouES.jpg | image_caption = | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Chordata]] | classis = [[Actinopterygii]] | ordo = [[Aulopiformes]] | familia = [[Synodontidae]] | genus = ''[[Synodus]]'' | species = '''''S. macrops''''' | binomial = ''Synodus macrops'' | binomial_authority = [[Shigeho Tanaka|S. Tanaka (I)]], 1917 }}
The '''triplecross lizardfish''' ''(Synodus macrops)'' is a type of [[lizardfish]] that lives mainly in the Indo-West Pacific.
==Information== The triplecross lizardfish can be found in a marine environment within a demersal depth range of about {{convert|35|-| 200|m|-1|abbr=on}}. This species is native to a tropical environment. The maximum recorded length of the Triplecross lizardfish as an unsexed male is about {{convert|20|cm|abbr=on}}. The common length of this species as an unsexed male is around {{convert|10|cm|abbr=on}}. The triplecross lizardfish can be found in the areas of Indo-West Pacific, Red Sea, India, Andaman Sea, eastward to southern Japan, and Australia. It is common in ranges from coastal sand flats to deep off-shore, but prefers deeper waters. It is used as a source of food. It is commonly caught and sold fresh or dried salted in markets.<ref name=FishBase>{{cite web|title=Synodus macrops Tanaka, 1917 Triplecross lizardfish|url=http://fishbase.sinica.edu.tw/Summary/SpeciesSummary.php?ID=8299|publisher=Fish Base|accessdate=17 May 2013}}</ref> This species is considered to be a benthic species. The Triplecross lizardfish serves as no threat to humans and it is considered to be harmless.<ref name=DiscoverLife>{{cite web|title=Synodus macrops Tanaka, 1917 TRIPLECROSS LIZARDFISH Big-eyed Lizardfish; Enigmatic Lizardfish|url=http://www.discoverlife.org/mp/20q?search=Synodus+macrops&l=spanish|publisher=Discover Life|accessdate=17 May 2013}}</ref> This species cannot be kept in an aquarium or be used for commercial trading for aquaria.<ref name=Guppies.ZA>{{cite web|title=Triplecross lizardfish (Synodus macrops) fish profile|url=http://www.guppies.za.net/triplecross-lizardfish-synodus-macrops-fish-profile.aspx|publisher=Guppies.ZA|accessdate=17 May 2013}}</ref>
